name: Overhead Press
instructions: Stand tall, brace your core, and press the barbell straight overhead while keeping your elbows slightly in front of the bar.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Lower dumbbells to chest level and press them upward, keeping wrists straight and elbows at 45°.

name: Incline Bench Press
instructions: Press the barbell from chest to overhead on a 30–45° incline bench. Control the descent.

name: Dumbbell Incline Bench
instructions: Perform like the incline barbell press but with dumbbells. Keep a steady rhythm.

name: Chin-ups
instructions: Pull your chin above the bar using an underhand grip. Control your descent.

name: Pull-ups
instructions: Use an overhand grip. Pull until your chin clears the bar, then lower under control.

name: Renegade Rows
instructions: From a push-up position on dumbbells, row one dumbbell to your side while stabilizing your core.

name: Russian Twists
instructions: Sit with heels raised, twist your torso to tap each side of your hips with a weight or hands.

name: Plate Overhead Lunge
instructions: Hold a plate overhead with arms locked. Step into lunges while keeping the plate steady overhead.

name: Goblet Squat
instructions: Hold a kettlebell or dumbbell at chest. Squat down keeping torso upright and heels flat.

name: Bodyweight Dips
instructions: Lower yourself between bars until elbows are 90°. Push back up without swinging.

name: Burpee to Renegade Row
instructions: Perform a burpee with push-up and row a dumbbell to your side at the bottom before jumping back up.

name: Dumbbell Lunges
instructions: Hold dumbbells at your side and lunge forward, lowering the back knee just above the floor.

name: Kettlebell Front Rack Lunge
instructions: Hold kettlebells in the front rack position and perform alternating lunges with an upright torso.

name: Farmers Carry
instructions: Carry heavy dumbbells or kettlebells at your side. Walk with a strong grip and upright posture.

name: Plank Rows
instructions: Hold a plank on dumbbells and row one arm at a time, avoiding hip rotation.

name: Overhead Plate Carry
instructions: Hold a plate locked out overhead. Walk steadily while bracing your core and staying upright.

name: Push-ups
instructions: Lower your chest to the floor with elbows at 45°. Push back to full extension.

name: Handstand Hold
instructions: Kick up to a wall-supported handstand. Keep your body tight and straight during the hold.

name: L-Sit
instructions: Support yourself on parallettes or dip bars. Hold legs straight in front at hip height.

name: Sumo Deadlift High Pulls
instructions: Start wide stance, pull barbell to chin after explosive hip extension. Keep elbows high.

name: Tabata Burpees
instructions: Perform Max Effort burpees 20s on, 10s rest. Complete 3 rounds. Repeat for 3 total Tabata cycles.

name: Tabata Pushups
instructions: Perform Max Effort push-ups 20s on, 10s rest. 3 rounds per set. Repeat for 3 Tabata sets.
